headline: Memory chip makers gain as Samsung delays DDR5 pricing amid price spike
summary: Investing.com -- Memory chip stocks jumped in Monday’s premarket trading after a report that Samsung Electronics has delayed setting contract prices for DDR5 memory chips as spot prices tripled.

headline: Wall Street futures rise on AI optimism, US-China trade truce
summary: The benchmark S&P 500 posted its sixth consecutive monthly gain in October, its longest such streak in four years, while the tech-heavy Nasdaq logged its longest streak since January 2018 after all the so-called "Magnificent Seven" companies that have reported their earnings so far pointed to a surge in AI spending.  Investors will have more clues on AI demand, as semiconductor firms including Advanced Micro Devices and Qualcomm report results this week.  U.S. President Donald Trump said AI giant Nvidia's most advanced chips will be reserved for U.S. companies and kept out of China and other countries.

headline: Heard on the Street Friday Recap: Market Streak
summary: Amazon soared. The e-commerce and cloud-computing giant’s shares hit a record high and ended the day 9.6% higher. While the company’s quarterly revenue outlook missed expectations, stronger growth in its cloud unit pleased investors.

headline: What Are Wall Street Analysts' Target Price for Western Digital Stock?
summary: Western Digital has significantly outpaced the broader market over the past year, and analysts remain strongly bullish on the stock’s prospects. However, the stock is currently trading above its mean price target.

headline: 3 S&P 500 Stocks That Concern Us
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is often seen as a benchmark for strong businesses, but that doesn’t mean every stock is worth owning. Some companies face significant challenges, whether it’s stagnating growth, heavy debt, or disruptive new competitors.
